          "key": "cck9i",
          "text": "​Benjamin Franklin: An American Life by Walter Isaacson (891 pages)\n​Walter Isaacson, like Robert Caro, is another one of the greatest living biographers (who I was lucky enough to interview on The Daily Stoic Podcast a few months back). I calculated that I have read 4,000 pages of his books, including Elon Musk, Einstein, Leonardo da Vinci, Steve Jobs, and Benjamin Franklin. I recommend all of his biographies, but what struck me about his book on Benjamin Franklin is that you think you know that Benjamin Franklin lived an incredible, crazy life and then you read this book and realize you don’t even know the half of it.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
